_Archived content (do not follow for new work):_

# Stack (obsolete)

- Monorepo with `apps/web` and `apps/api`
- Frontend: Next.js + TypeScript + Tailwind
- Backend: NestJS + TypeScript
- Database: MongoDB
- Shared domain types: `packages/types`

# Product constraints (still valid at domain level)

- Private login-first app
- Two buckets: `catalog` and `wishlist`
- Media types: `movie`, `tv`, `album`, `book`, `game`
- Ratings are read-only external metadata only
- No email verification or password reset
- Barcode scanning is best-effort candidate matching, never assume exact auto-match

# Architecture rules (superseded by Go monolith)

- Frontend must never call third-party metadata providers directly
- Backend owns auth, sessions, provider integrations, normalization, barcode lookup, caching, and permission checks
- Do not replace MongoDB with Postgres
- Do not collapse frontend and backend into separate deployable services for *new* work—the shipped product is one Go binary
